>
  <h2>What is a Website?</h2>
  <p>
    A <strong>website</strong> is a collection of web pages stored on a powerful computer called a <strong>server</strong>. You visit it using a <strong>browser</strong> (like Chrome, Firefox, or Safari) by typing its address — called a <strong>URL</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>What Are Websites Made Of?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>🏗️ <strong>HTML</strong> — The structure and content (text, headings, images, links).</li>
    <li>🎨 <strong>CSS</strong> — The styling (colors, fonts, layouts — what makes it look pretty!).</li>
    <li>⚡ <strong>JavaScript</strong> — The interactivity (buttons, animations, games).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What is a URL?</h2>
  <p>
    A <strong>URL (Uniform Resource Locator)</strong> is the address of a webpage. For example: <code>https://codescompiler.com</code>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>https://</code> — The protocol (how data is sent securely).</li>
    <li><code>codescompiler</code> — The domain name (the website's name).</li>
    <li><code>.com</code> — The extension (tells you the type of site).</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    A website is like a book. HTML is the words and pictures, CSS is the cover design and fonts, and JavaScript makes the pages interactive — like pop-up quizzes or animations!
  </blockquote>

